{"lemma":"أَبْتَعِ","slug":"أَبْتَعِ","root":"ب.ت.ع","root_slug":"ب-ت-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ت-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1723"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1723","headword_ar":"اَبْتَعُ","root":"btE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batiEN","text_ar":"بَتِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places.       -A2-  It is also a word used as a corroborative: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA","text_ar":"جَاوُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomaEuwna A^akotaEuwna A^abotaEuwna","text_ar":"اَجْمَعُونَ اَكْتَعُونَ اَبْتَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came, all of them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a Alqawomu A^akotaEuwna","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ القَوْمُ اَكْتَعُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abotaEuwna A^aboSaEuwna","text_ar":"اَبْتَعُونَ اَبْصَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men, came, all of them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AHeyth:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA kul~uhumo A^ajomaEuwna A^akotaEuwna A^abotaEuwna","text_ar":"جَاوُوا كُلُّهُمْ اَجْمَعُونَ اَكْتَعُونَ اَبْتَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they came, all of them, all together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: these words which follow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AjmEwn","text_ar":"اجمعون"},{"kind":"text","text":"being imitative sequents to it, not occurring save after it [in the order above]: (O, K:) or one may begin with whichsoever of them he will, after it. (Ibn-Keysán, K.) And [the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batoEaA='u","text_ar":"بَتْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqabiylapu kul~uhaA jamoEaA='u","text_ar":"القَبِيلَةُ كُلُّهَا جَمْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katoEaA='u baSoEaA='u batoEaA='u","text_ar":"كَتْعَا=ءُ بَصْعَا=ءُ بَتْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tribe, all of it, all together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuvoEA='u","text_ar":"كُثْعا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(with damm and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buSoEA'u","text_ar":"بُصْعاءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"butoEA'u","text_ar":"بُتْعاءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And [the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batoEaA='u","text_ar":"بَتْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"butaEu","text_ar":"بُتَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"batoEaAwaAtN","text_ar":"بَتْعَاوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~isaA='u","text_ar":"النِّسَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":150},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~uhun~a jumaEu kutaEu buSaEu butaEu","text_ar":"كُلُّهُنَّ جُمَعُ كُتَعُ بُصَعُ بُتَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The women, all of them, all together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumaEN","text_ar":"جُمَعٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutaEN buSaEN butaEN","text_ar":"كُتَعٌ بُصَعٌ بُتَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though it is well known that each of these is determinate, and imperfectly declinable]. (K.) It is only necessary that he who mentions all these words should mention first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~","text_ar":"كُلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and follow it with the word formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j m E","text_ar":"ج م ع"},{"kind":"text","text":", then add the rest in whatsoever order he will; but the more approved way is to put the word formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k t E","text_ar":"ك ت ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"before the rest. (TA.) Fr mentions the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojabniY AlqaSoru A^ajomaEa","text_ar":"اَعْجَبنِى القَصْرُ اَجْمَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[The palace pleased me, all of it, or altogether], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAru jamoEaA='a","text_ar":"الدَّارُ جَمْعَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the house, all of it, or altogether], with the accus. case, as denotative of state; but does not allow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomaEuwna","text_ar":"اَجْمَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumaEu","text_ar":"جُمَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be used otherwise than as corroboratives: IDrst, however, allows"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomaEiyna","text_ar":"اَجْمَعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be used as a denotative of state; and this is correct; and accord. to both these ways is related the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSal~uwA juluwsFA A^ajomaEiyna","text_ar":"فَصَلُّوا جُلُوسًا اَجْمَعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomaEuwna","text_ar":"اَجْمَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[And pray ye sitting, all of you, or all together]; though some make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AjmEyn","text_ar":"اجمعين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here] to be a corroborative of a pronoun understood in the accus. case, as though the speaker said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoniykumo","text_ar":"اَعْنِيكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomaEiyna","text_ar":"اَجْمَعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[I mean you, all of you, or all together]. (K.) [But see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomEu","text_ar":"اَجْمعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","AHeyth","O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}